Condon Wind Power, LLC
FERC Electric Tariff No. 1
(Market-Based Rate Tariff)
1. Availability. Under this Tariff, Condon Wind Power, LLC (???Condon Wind Power??? or ???Seller???) will make available to any purchaser for resale wholesale sales of electric energy and capacity.
(a) Third-Party Ancillary Services: Seller offers: Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider???s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and capacity by Condon Wind Power, to the extent such sales and/or resales are not otherwise subject to a particular Tariff of Condon Wind Power.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at the rates established between the purchaser and Condon Wind Power.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established between the purchaser and Condon Wind Power.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Condon Wind Power shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Condon Wind Power???s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Condon Wind Power to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Condon Wind Power???s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Condon Wind Power???s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller???s market-based rate authority is not subject to any limitations. Condon Wind Power has been granted the following waivers and blanket authorization: (a) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission???s regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (b) waiver of Parts 41, 101, and 141 of the Commission???s regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, with the exception of 18 C.F.R. ???? 141.14 and 141.15; and (c) blanket approval as to Section 204 of the Federal Power Act and Part 34 of the Commission???s regulations for all future issuances of securities and debt and assumption of liabilities. See Condon Wind Power, LLC, 97 FERC ?? 61,281, at 62,280-81 (2001).
7. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a).
